column1: 1 - Metering Type is selected by the applicant, and is subject to project/account eligibility and approval.

2 - Applications received prior to the NYSSIR effective 4/29/16 were processed under the applicable prior version of NYSSIR.  Therefore, for projects with a system size greater than 50 kW, the Application Review was conducted and approved as part of the 15 Business Day Preliminary Review.

3 - 2021 Observed Company Holidays: New Year's Day (1/1), President's Day (2/15), Good Friday (4/2), Memorial Day (5/31), Independence Day (7/5), Labor Day (9/6), Thanksgiving Day & Day After (11/25, 11/26), Christmas Eve & Christmas Day (12/23, 12/24), New Year's Day (12/31)

4 - Actual Utility Project Costs include the cost of installing a dedicated transformer and/or other safety equipment to accommodate the customers distributed generation installation in addition to the Actual Customer Project Costs.  It does not include administrative fees, non-CESIR technical review, or meter changes.

5 - For applications receiving final interconnection approval on or after the NYSSIR, effective 4/29/16, the Verification Testing or Final Acceptance Date is the date that the utility witnessed the verification test, or if the utility has opted not to witness the test, it is the date that all necessary final interconnection documentation were received. This includes notification of system completion, proof of electrical inspection and verification test documentation. For projects interconnected prior to 4/29/16, this date may also be the date the witness test was requested.
